included.name: Human Factor Studies on Gestural Interaction: Past, Present and Future
included.description: Gestural interaction is a recently developed natural interaction manner, in which users interact with the machine directly with their body movements. The human factor (HF) studies are a core aspect in studies of gestural interaction; however, so far the HF studies of the gestural interaction have not been systematically summarized. The current study closed this gap by reviewing the extant HF studies on the gestural interaction. We first introduced the history of gestural interaction, and then summarized the current interaction manners of Kinect and the Kinect-based human factor assessments. Finally, we discussed the potential shortcomings of the current gestural interaction system as well as the possible HF research directions.
